472
00:21:00.845 --> 00:21:02.555
I'll take Jay because we're not old.

473
00:21:02.639 --> 00:21:04.808
And Charles should take Bash
because they're both. well.

474
00:21:04.891 --> 00:21:06.768
what we used to call "the weird kid."

475
00:21:07.644 --> 00:21:09.145
[clicking tongue]
Aw.

476
00:21:12.315 --> 00:21:15.193
Camila! I-- I just have
a few more questions.

477
00:21:15.277 --> 00:21:16.987
Can I give you a tour?

478
00:21:17.070 --> 00:21:18.071
Fine.

479
00:21:18.822 --> 00:21:22.993
If you can stop yelling.
a tour before dinner.

480
00:21:23.076 --> 00:21:25.745
Dinner!
I said we need dinner.

481
00:21:25.829 --> 00:21:28.248
Of course. a party at 7:00
means dinner.

482
00:21:29.040 --> 00:21:31.126
Thank you. Bash!
Gimme a hand?

483
00:21:32.294 --> 00:21:34.212
If the servants don't mind.

484
00:21:34.296 --> 00:21:37.173
[chuckling]
Oh. the servants aren't gonna mind.

485
00:21:40.218 --> 00:21:41.219
[Jay] Beer?

486
00:21:46.725 --> 00:21:48.685
So. Jay...

487
00:21:49.686 --> 00:21:50.770
[can popping]

488
00:21:50.854 --> 00:21:52.814
How'd you lose the finger?

489
00:21:55.108 --> 00:21:57.027
How'd those two old guys
become your best friends?

490
00:21:57.944 --> 00:21:58.945
Nice.

491
00:21:59.487 --> 00:22:01.906
[♪ plucky curious music playing]

492
00:22:02.324 --> 00:22:03.325
[gasps]

493
00:22:05.285 --> 00:22:06.661
So. how well do you know Jay?

494
00:22:06.745 --> 00:22:09.414
Have you-- have you two
been playing together for long?

495
00:22:09.497 --> 00:22:11.708
All I know about Jay

496
00:22:11.791 --> 00:22:15.003
is he has a tantrum
like a toddler when he loses...

497
00:22:15.086 --> 00:22:17.714
-Ooh.
-...which is tragic and amusing.

498
00:22:17.797 --> 00:22:20.842
I'm sorry. but every room

499
00:22:20.925 --> 00:22:23.720
-in this house needs me.
-Oh.

500
00:22:23.803 --> 00:22:27.182
Are those the Statler and Waldorf
balconies on your wall?

501
00:22:27.265 --> 00:22:30.977
Ha! Well. I'm-- I'm a theater director.
[chuckles]

502
00:22:31.061 --> 00:22:34.397
So. you thought. "I should put
theater directing on my walls"?

503
00:22:34.856 --> 00:22:35.857
[inhales sharply]

504
00:22:36.274 --> 00:22:39.861
Well. but. the-- the beauty of this place
is really its stories.

505
00:22:39.944 --> 00:22:41.988
Uh. like my ex-wife. uh.
loved these drapes.

506
00:22:42.072 --> 00:22:45.241
so I fought to keep them out of spite.
[laughing]

507
00:22:45.325 --> 00:22:47.494
Not necessarily my finest moment.

508
00:22:47.577 --> 00:22:51.748
but. uh. not all the stories
in here are great.

509
00:22:53.249 --> 00:22:56.795
[gasps]
Well. this looks great.

510
00:22:57.587 --> 00:23:01.007
This<i> is </i>great.
It's my new wife.

511
00:23:02.884 --> 00:23:04.803
And she moved in... to all this?

512
00:23:06.513 --> 00:23:08.973
Uh. well. n-- Uh. not yet.

513
00:23:09.057 --> 00:23:12.060
but. uh. you know. I mean...

514
00:23:12.143 --> 00:23:13.144
[food sizzling]

515
00:23:13.228 --> 00:23:15.230
I love <i>duck à l'orange.</i>

516
00:23:15.313 --> 00:23:17.690
During the war
we only had duck at Christmas.

517
00:23:17.774 --> 00:23:19.651
Oh. and-- and which war was that?

518
00:23:19.734 --> 00:23:23.196
"Three sprigs of parsley."
Uh. I'll chop.

519
00:23:24.656 --> 00:23:26.366
[knife clinking]

520
00:23:27.659 --> 00:23:29.869
[knife banging]

521
00:23:31.287 --> 00:23:32.872
Haven't cooked in decades.

522
00:23:32.956 --> 00:23:35.834
So. you haven't used
a-- a cleaver in a while.

523
00:23:35.917 --> 00:23:37.794
You know anybody else who might
have used a cleaver?

524
00:23:37.877 --> 00:23:39.379
-Anybody?
-Isn't it interesting?

525
00:23:39.462 --> 00:23:42.632
None of us will leave behind
written recipes.

526
00:23:42.715 --> 00:23:45.927
Future generations will just have
bookmarks on chef robots.

527
00:23:46.010 --> 00:23:48.638
Yeah. it's. uh... it's true. it's sad.

528
00:23:48.721 --> 00:23:50.473
You know. the-- the times are changing.

529
00:23:50.557 --> 00:23:53.560
especially for us old guys in our--
How old did you say you were?

530
00:23:53.643 --> 00:23:55.019
That depends on the organ.

531
00:23:56.020 --> 00:24:00.984
Charles. wallowing takes
six years off your life.

532
00:24:01.067 --> 00:24:04.320
Dorothy Parker told me that.
She took my virginity.

533
00:24:04.404 --> 00:24:07.991
Point is. you're only old
if you don't change with the times.

534
00:24:08.074 --> 00:24:10.910
You know.
technology's helped me stay young.

535
00:24:10.994 --> 00:24:13.163
But reinvention is the real key.

536
00:24:14.372 --> 00:24:17.250
Yeah. that-- it-- it takes
a lot of energy keeping up.

537
00:24:18.251 --> 00:24:19.419
Yeah. it does.

538
00:24:19.502 --> 00:24:22.505
Every time I've put a wife
in assisted living and had to start over.

539
00:24:22.589 --> 00:24:24.591
I've had moments of doubt
that I could do it.

540
00:24:24.674 --> 00:24:25.967
But I did.

541
00:24:26.050 --> 00:24:27.051
And you can.

542
00:24:27.927 --> 00:24:29.637
Well. thank you.

543
00:24:29.721 --> 00:24:32.974
Now. how much orange zest
goes in great-gran's--

544
00:24:33.057 --> 00:24:34.058
-[knife banging]
-[yelps]

545
00:24:34.142 --> 00:24:36.936
Oh! No. no. no. no.
no. no. no!

546
00:24:37.020 --> 00:24:38.897
[sauce simmering]

547
00:24:38.980 --> 00:24:40.982
My great-gran is gone!

548
00:24:41.065 --> 00:24:42.609
It's gone.

549
00:24:43.443 --> 00:24:44.527
-No!
-[phone pings]

550
00:24:44.611 --> 00:24:45.612
How much orange zest

551
00:24:45.695 --> 00:24:48.656
is in Charles-Haden Savage's
great-gran's <i>duck à l'orange </i>recipe?

552
00:24:48.740 --> 00:24:49.866
[phone pinging]

553
00:24:49.949 --> 00:24:51.826
[chat voice]
<i>There are one-and-a-half teaspoons</i>

554
00:24:51.910 --> 00:24:54.454
<i>of orange zest in that recipe.</i>

555
00:24:54.537 --> 00:24:56.247
How did it know that?

556
00:24:57.040 --> 00:24:58.958
-[phone pings]
-Show me Charles-Haden Savage

557
00:24:59.042 --> 00:25:00.627
making <i>duck à l'orange.</i>

558
00:25:00.710 --> 00:25:02.921
[Regis Philbin] [on phone]
<i>That sounds like a lot of zest. Brazzos.</i>

559
00:25:03.004 --> 00:25:04.422
[Charles]
<i>I'm zesty. Regis.</i>

560
00:25:04.506 --> 00:25:06.049
<i>Yes. you're a multi-talented guy.</i>

561
00:25:06.132 --> 00:25:08.343
<i>I admire guys like that.</i>
<i>that could do more than one thing.</i>

562
00:25:08.426 --> 00:25:10.011
<i>-I just revel in it.</i>
-[audience laughter]

563
00:25:10.094 --> 00:25:12.347
<i>Probably in ten minutes.</i>
<i>something unbelievable is gonna happen.</i>

564
00:25:12.430 --> 00:25:15.517
[Regis]<i> Why do I think it's gonna be me</i>
<i>making your </i>duck à l'orange?

565
00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:17.685
[Charles]
<i>Well. Regis. because you're psychic.</i>

566
00:25:17.769 --> 00:25:18.978
<i>We're gonna take a commercial break</i>

567
00:25:19.062 --> 00:25:21.231
<i>-and make it happen in the next segment.</i>
-[audience applauding]

568
00:25:21.314 --> 00:25:22.357
[video stops]

569
00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:24.526
I forgot I did that.

570
00:25:24.609 --> 00:25:26.569
My great-gran lives on.

571
00:25:26.653 --> 00:25:27.654
Thank you.

572
00:25:28.571 --> 00:25:30.573
This is why I do what I do.

573
00:25:30.657 --> 00:25:34.744
In the right hands. technology should keep
the past alive. preserved.

574
00:25:34.827 --> 00:25:38.331
like I'm preserved every night
floating in my tank of collagen.

575
00:25:38.414 --> 00:25:40.750
[knife banging]

576
00:25:40.833 --> 00:25:43.836
-I also had a sad home.
-[Oliver] Ah.

577
00:25:43.920 --> 00:25:45.672
My first one.

578
00:25:45.755 --> 00:25:48.675
A young girl with a deep love of beauty.

579
00:25:48.758 --> 00:25:52.512
born to a casino magnate
and his former showgirl wife.

580
00:25:52.595 --> 00:25:55.348
raised amidst a sea of hot pink

581
00:25:55.431 --> 00:25:57.267
in Reno.

582
00:25:57.350 --> 00:25:58.810
Eww. so sorry.

583
00:25:58.893 --> 00:26:01.479
The moment I turned 18.

584
00:26:01.563 --> 00:26:04.607
I moved... to Connecticut.

585
00:26:04.691 --> 00:26:06.776
-Oh.
-Leaving that home

586
00:26:06.859 --> 00:26:09.112
jump-started my mission
to beautify the world.

587
00:26:09.195 --> 00:26:11.781
and it turned me into a billionaire.

588
00:26:11.864 --> 00:26:15.201
-[gasps softly]
-And I started with nothing.

589
00:26:17.704 --> 00:26:19.831
So. are-- are you saying that
Loretta and I

590
00:26:19.914 --> 00:26:22.125
should start fresh?
Get a new place?

591
00:26:22.208 --> 00:26:25.503
-These bones are remarkable.
-Ah.

592
00:26:25.587 --> 00:26:28.840
You just need to change everything.

593
00:26:31.384 --> 00:26:33.595
-[can popping]
-[Jay sighs]

594
00:26:33.678 --> 00:26:36.180
[Mabel] So. uh. come on. the finger?

595
00:26:36.264 --> 00:26:37.473
I gotta know.

596
00:26:37.557 --> 00:26:38.558
[sighs]

597
00:26:38.641 --> 00:26:41.227
The only crime I'm guilty of
is being an embarrassing nepo baby

598
00:26:41.311 --> 00:26:45.398
who's trying to do some good
with his ancestors' blood money.

599
00:26:45.481 --> 00:26:46.858
Yeah. and how's that going?

600
00:26:46.941 --> 00:26:50.278
I started my own nonprofit.
hired a CEO.

601
00:26:50.361 --> 00:26:54.282
a friend of mine I trusted.
who then took all the money.

602
00:26:54.365 --> 00:26:56.034
Everyone thinks I'm a swindler.

603
00:26:56.117 --> 00:26:58.620
but really. I'm just shit
at knowing who to trust.

604
00:26:59.704 --> 00:27:01.956
I'm sure it'll happen again.

605
00:27:02.040 --> 00:27:03.583
Then. why keep trying?

606
00:27:06.210 --> 00:27:10.131
Because I wanna prove to everyone
that I'm not a... fuck up.

607
00:27:12.592 --> 00:27:15.428
[sighs deeply]

608
00:27:15.511 --> 00:27:19.849
Are you aware
of the pop sensation THĒ?

609
00:27:20.725 --> 00:27:23.519
Uh. the "The" girl?
Yeah. why?

610
00:27:23.603 --> 00:27:27.440
She is someone <i>I </i>incorrectly trusted.

611
00:27:27.523 --> 00:27:31.736
She couldn't be more frustrating.

612
00:27:31.819 --> 00:27:35.823
and I... I can't stop
wanting to impress her.

613
00:27:35.907 --> 00:27:40.370
So. I lied and said we were
getting a deal at Wondify.

614
00:27:40.453 --> 00:27:41.829
and we aren't.

615
00:27:41.913 --> 00:27:44.248
So. now I have to try
to make that happen.

616
00:27:44.332 --> 00:27:45.958
I'm sure it won't.

617
00:27:46.042 --> 00:27:48.711
And I hate myself for that.

618
00:27:49.504 --> 00:27:52.340
[singing] <i>♪ Wish that you were me.</i>
<i>bet you wish that you were me ♪</i>

619
00:27:52.423 --> 00:27:54.133
-I will literally kill you.
-[Jay laughs]

620
00:27:54.217 --> 00:27:56.094
She wrote that.
I feel like. about me.

621
00:27:56.177 --> 00:27:57.929
[Jay] It's really good.
It's catchy.

622
00:28:00.890 --> 00:28:03.351
I <i>was </i>playing with these bozos
the night Nicky died.

623
00:28:03.434 --> 00:28:05.228
but I did not kill anyone.

624
00:28:06.312 --> 00:28:08.356
So. what happened with your finger?

625
00:28:10.066 --> 00:28:14.737
Just another bad decision
in a long line of bad decisions.

626
00:28:14.821 --> 00:28:17.824
[♪ bubbly music playing]

627
00:28:19.617 --> 00:28:21.744
[Oliver]
While we have a quiet moment.

628
00:28:21.828 --> 00:28:25.206
I wanna help you make sure
you stay out of our little story.

629
00:28:25.998 --> 00:28:28.376
But what happened
to Jay's finger?

630
00:28:30.878 --> 00:28:31.879
Fine.

631
00:28:32.880 --> 00:28:35.216
The night Lester died.

632
00:28:35.299 --> 00:28:37.885
Nicky showed up
with this cleaver.

633
00:28:37.969 --> 00:28:39.178
[knife banging]

634
00:28:39.262 --> 00:28:41.097
Wa-- Was he mad at someone?
Maybe Jay?

635
00:28:41.180 --> 00:28:45.351
He was livid and raving
about the film <i>"Goodfellows"?</i>

636
00:28:45.435 --> 00:28:48.855
He had an inordinate amount
of white powder

637
00:28:48.938 --> 00:28:50.481
under his nose.

638
00:28:50.565 --> 00:28:53.234
I'd call it a Snow White white.

639
00:28:53.317 --> 00:28:56.279
or perhaps
a Santa's beard white.

640
00:28:56.362 --> 00:28:57.697
He was nuts.

641
00:28:57.780 --> 00:28:59.949
He was gonna hit someone.
I tried to stop him.

642
00:29:00.032 --> 00:29:02.034
I mean.
Bash is covered in baby skin.

643
00:29:02.118 --> 00:29:03.578
but he's pretty old.

644
00:29:03.661 --> 00:29:06.789
Well. I tried to calm him down.
but Jay had to be the hero.

645
00:29:06.873 --> 00:29:09.292
and so Nicky-- "chh!"--
chopped off his finger.

646
00:29:09.375 --> 00:29:10.376
[stifled chuckle]

647
00:29:10.877 --> 00:29:13.463
I obviously left
because of the mess.

648
00:29:14.380 --> 00:29:17.216
And also. it's rude to be
the last to leave a party. so...

649
00:29:17.300 --> 00:29:21.220
I told Jay not to escalate. but chop-chop.
Then we all ran out.

650
00:29:21.304 --> 00:29:24.348
There wasn't time to look for it.
which is why I went back.

651
00:29:25.558 --> 00:29:27.727
It'd be nice not to have a finger
floating around. ya know?

652
00:29:27.810 --> 00:29:29.312
You didn't happen to see it
in there. did you?

653
00:29:29.395 --> 00:29:31.063
-[door opens]
-[oven chimes]

654
00:29:31.147 --> 00:29:32.940
Okay.
<i>Duck à l'orange</i>

655
00:29:33.024 --> 00:29:34.942
is ready in two hours and 45 minutes.

656
00:29:35.026 --> 00:29:37.487
-Who's hungry?
-I don't eat after 11 a.m..

657
00:29:37.570 --> 00:29:39.530
but have we answered
all your questions?

658
00:29:39.614 --> 00:29:42.867
Well. yes. I learned that Nicky
chopped off Jay's finger.

659
00:29:42.950 --> 00:29:46.370
and then Bash. Camila.
and Jay ran out.

660
00:29:46.454 --> 00:29:48.664
-[Mabel] Yeah. that's what Jay said.
-[Oliver] And Lester and Nicky

661
00:29:48.748 --> 00:29:50.041
were still alive. so...

662
00:29:50.124 --> 00:29:52.794
Huh. look at you two
not lying to pin it on me.

663
00:29:52.877 --> 00:29:55.338
-You do care.
-Case closed.

664
00:29:55.421 --> 00:29:57.048
And now that we've cleared this up.

665
00:29:57.131 --> 00:30:00.176
I trust I won't hear my name
on future episodes.

666
00:30:00.259 --> 00:30:03.888
Okay. <i>duck à l'orange</i>
in two hours and 44 minutes.

667
00:30:03.971 --> 00:30:06.349
Ah. [sucking teeth]
Next time.

668
00:30:06.432 --> 00:30:09.644
Forgot I have some friends
coming over to do some rock climbing.

669
00:30:09.727 --> 00:30:11.270
Mabel...

670
00:30:11.354 --> 00:30:12.355
thanks.

671
00:30:13.648 --> 00:30:14.941
It was a really nice talk.

672
00:30:18.569 --> 00:30:21.489
Touching food again was pleasant.

673
00:30:21.572 --> 00:30:23.491
[door opens]

674
00:30:23.574 --> 00:30:25.076
Enjoy the remodel.

675
00:30:26.327 --> 00:30:27.745
[Oliver]
Wait. what remodel?

676
00:30:28.204 --> 00:30:31.207
[♪ light music playing]

677
00:30:31.290 --> 00:30:32.291
[door closes]

678
00:30:33.459 --> 00:30:35.837
Wow. this really is much better.

679
00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:37.505
[Charles]
How did we not hear anything?

680
00:30:37.588 --> 00:30:39.882
She's a home decor witch!

681
00:30:41.592 --> 00:30:42.593
[Mabel sighs]

682
00:30:45.388 --> 00:30:46.389
[cutlery clinking]

683
00:30:47.390 --> 00:30:49.725
[mouth full] This is better.
The hot glue fumes

684
00:30:49.809 --> 00:30:52.395
from my apartment
jump-started my hangover.

685
00:30:52.478 --> 00:30:54.146
Does champagne expire?

686
00:30:54.230 --> 00:30:56.732
Oh. you should really
lay off the alcohol.

687
00:30:56.816 --> 00:30:59.277
Uh. Bash says
it inflames your enzymes.

688
00:30:59.360 --> 00:31:01.404
Now. which war would you think
was going on

689
00:31:01.487 --> 00:31:04.156
when Dorothy Parker
was in her sexual prime?

690
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:06.284
First sexual prime. or second?

691
00:31:06.367 --> 00:31:10.162
How crazy is it that we have
Jay Pflug's finger in your freezer?

692
00:31:10.246 --> 00:31:12.081
At least we figured that out.

693
00:31:12.164 --> 00:31:15.042
So. we're gonna believe
these three?

694
00:31:15.126 --> 00:31:17.253
Oh. please. Camila is no killer.

695
00:31:17.336 --> 00:31:20.298
Although. I felt like I was spending
a couple of hours

696
00:31:20.381 --> 00:31:23.968
with a cross between Ann-Margret
and Nanette Fabray. so I almost died.

697
00:31:24.051 --> 00:31:25.970
[laughing. barking]

698
00:31:27.597 --> 00:31:28.890
Jay didn't do it.

699
00:31:28.973 --> 00:31:30.975
He was just trying
to protect everyone.

700
00:31:31.058 --> 00:31:34.729
He's. um... sweeter than I expected.

701
00:31:34.812 --> 00:31:36.063
Mabel...

702
00:31:37.231 --> 00:31:39.066
did your eyelashes just flutter?

703
00:31:39.150 --> 00:31:42.486
Oliver. Jay makes
Mabel's eyelashes flutter.

704
00:31:42.570 --> 00:31:45.364
No. I'm n--
Shut up. I'm not fluttering.

705
00:31:45.448 --> 00:31:48.618
It's just maybe we should
give him his finger back.

706
00:31:48.701 --> 00:31:50.661
Crushing on a suspect. Mabel?

707
00:31:50.745 --> 00:31:52.538
This is really a Charles storyline.

708
00:31:52.622 --> 00:31:53.831
-isn't it?
-Ugh.

709
00:31:53.915 --> 00:31:55.750
-[email notification chimes]
-If both of you couple up.

710
00:31:55.833 --> 00:31:59.545
that leaves me birding with Vince.
or getting a drink with a robot.

711
00:31:59.629 --> 00:32:02.673
[gasps] Oh. my God. you guys.
